OL,4,Ccity hosted Pan-African Congress
OL,6,FCarol Ann Whitehead with Heritage
OL,7,FOperations at Portico Museum said:
OL,8,F"The congress had been held in places
OL,9,Flike Paris and so on, so it was quite
OL,10,Fnice to have it in a 'people's venue',
OL,11,Fa people's location.
OL,13,F"In 1945, when these African American,
OL,14,FAfricans, Caribbeans and black British
OL,15,Fcame together to talk about moving
OL,16,Fforward, to drop the shackles of
OL,17,FImperialism, to drop the shackles of
OL,18,Fcolonialism, for doing things for
OL,19,Fthemselves.
